README.md

Awesome

   A curated list of awesome Perl5 frameworks, libraries and software.
   Inspired by [https://github.com/avelino/awesome-go]awesome-go.

   Not Perl6 modules ;-P

Another module list

   We also recommend these lists.
     * [https://github.com/EnlightenedPerlOrganisation/task-kensho]Task::K
       ensho
     * [http://perlmaven.com/perl-based-open-source-products]PerlMaven.com
       list of Perl Software
     * [https://github.com/eserte/srezic-misc/blob/master/cpan_in_a_nutshe
       ll/cpan_in_a_nutshell.pod]Slaven's CPAN in a nutshell
     * Many Task::** Modules. (ex. Task::Plack, Task::BeLike::...)

Contents

     * Awesome Perl
          + Args
          + Audio
          + Benchmarks
          + Caches
          + Class Builder
          + CLI
          + Cloud
          + Container
          + Data Format
          + Database
          + Database Drivers
               o Relational Databases
               o NoSQL Databases
          + Date & Time
          + Devices
          + DevOps
          + Email
          + Event Loops
          + Exception Handling
          + File Manipulation
          + Form Frameworks
          + Images
          + List Manipulation
          + Logging
          + Module Development
          + Network
          + ORM
          + Package Management
          + Processes and Threads
          + Profiling
          + Protocol
          + Queueing
          + REST Frameworks
          + Science/Numerics
          + Template Engines
          + Testing
               o Testing Frameworks
               o Test Double
               o Coverage
          + Tools
          + Video
          + Web Frameworks
               o Middlewares
          + Web Frameworks-Like
          + Web Scraping

Args

   Libraries for argument manifestation and validation.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Data::Validator]Data::Validator - Rule
       based validator on type constraint system.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Params::Util]Params::Util - Simple,
       compact and correct param-checking functions.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Params::Validate]Params::Validate -
       Validate method/function parameters.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Smart::Args]Smart::Args

Audio

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Audio::CD]Audio::CD - Interface to
       libcdaudio (cd + cddb)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Audio::Wav]Audio::Wav - Modules for
       reading & writing Microsoft WAV files.

Benchmarks

   Libraries for benchmarking
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Benchmark]Benchmark
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Dumbbench]Dumbbench
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Parallel::Benchmark]Parallel::Benchmark -
       Benchmark in multiprocesses

Caches

   Libraries to talk to Cache Softwares
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI]CHI - Unified cache handling
       interface, think DBI for caches
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI::Driver::DBI]CHI::Driver::DBI - DBI
       driver for CHI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI::Driver::DBIC]CHI::Driver::DBIC -
       DBIx::Class driver for CHI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI::Driver::Memcached]CHI::Driver::Memca
       ched - Memcached driver for CHI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI::Driver::MongoDB]CHI::Driver::MongoDB
       - MongoDB driver for CHI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CHI::Driver::Redis]CHI::Driver::Redis -
       Redis driver for CHI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Catalyst::Plugin::Session::Store::CHI]Cat
       alyst::Plugin::Session::Store::CHI - Use CHI module to handle
       storage backend for session data
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CGI::Application::Plugin::CHI]CGI::Applic
       ation::Plugin::CHI - CGI-App plugin for CHI caching interface
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mojolicious::Plugin::CHI]Mojolicious::Plu
       gin::CHI - Interact with CHI caches

Class Builder

   Libraries to support writing classes and meta programming
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Class::Accessor::Lite]Class::Accessor::Li
       te - Simple accessor generator.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Class::Accessor::Lite::Lazy]Class::Access
       or::Lite::Lazy - Generate lazy accessors.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Homer]Homer - Simple Prototype-based
       object system.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mo]Mo - Micro Objects. Mo is less.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Moo]Moo - Class builder supporting meta
       programming.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Moose]Moose - The one and only, Moose.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mouse]Mouse - Yet another class builder
       like Moo/Moose.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Object::Tiny]Object::Tiny - A class
       builder that is terse, fast, and tiny.

CLI

   Libraries for developing CLI applications
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/App::Cmd]App::Cmd - Write command line
       apps with less suffering.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Getopt::Long]Getopt::Long - Extended
       processing of command line options.

Cloud

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/AWS::CloudFront]AWS::CloudFront -
       Lightweight interface to Amazon CloudFront CDN
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/AWS::S3]AWS::S3 - Lightweight interface
       to Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::Amazon::EC2]Net::Amazon::EC2 -
       Interface to the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) environment.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::AWS::SES]Net::AWS::SES - Perl
       extension that implements Amazon Simple Email Service (SES) client
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/WebService::DigitalOcean]WebService::Digi
       talOcean - Access the DigitalOcean RESTful API (v2)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/WebService::Dropbox]WebService::Dropbox -
       Interface to Dropbox API

Container

   Libraries for Singleton Pattern implementation.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Object::Container]Object::Container

Data Format

   Libraries for serializing, formatting and parsing
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Data::Dumper::Simple]Data::Dumper::Simple
       - Reduce and faster Data::Dumper and eval() equivalent
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Data::MessagePack]Data::MessagePack
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/JSON::PP]JSON::PP
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/JSON::XS]JSON::XS
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Sereal]Sereal
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Storable]Storable
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::CSV]Text::CSV
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::CSV_XS]Text::CSV_XS
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::Markdown]Text::Markdown
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/TOML]TOML
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/XML::LibXML]XML::LibXML
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/XML::Compile::Schema]XML::Compile::Schema
       - Interpret schema elements and types: create processors for XML
       messages.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/XML::Compile::SOAP]XML::Compile::SOAP -
       Implements the SOAP 1.1 protocol, client side.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/XML::Compile::WSDL]XML::Compile::WSDL -
       Use SOAP with a WSDL version 1.1 communication specification file.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/YAML]YAML

Database

   Libraries for dealing with relational databases
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBI]DBI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Connector]DBIx::Connector - Fast,
       safe DBI connection and transaction management
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Handler]DBIx::Handler - Fork-safe
       DBI handler
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Inspector]DBIx::Inspector
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::QueryLog]DBIx::QueryLog
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Sunny]DBIx::Sunny - Useful DBI
       Wrapper
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::TransactionManager]DBIx::Transactio
       nManager

Database Drivers

   Libraries for using specific database products

Relational Databases

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::CSV]DBD::CSV
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::Firebird]DBD::Firebird
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::mysql]DBD::mysql
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::ODBC]DBD::ODBC - Any ODBC Driver.
       MS-SQL w/ placeholders
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::Oracle]DBD::Oracle - Oracle database
       driver for the DBI module
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::Pg]DBD::Pg - PostgreSQL driver for
       DBI.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::SQLite]DBD::SQLite
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBD::Sybase]DBD::Sybase - Sybase and
       MS-SQL. No placeholders w/ MS-SQL though

NoSQL Databases

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Cache::Memcached::Fast]Cache::Memcached::
       Fast
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mango]Mango - Pure-Perl non-blocking I/O
       MongoDB driver
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Redis]Redis
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Redis::Fast]Redis::Fast - Perl wrapper
       around hiredis driver
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Search::Elasticsearch]Search::Elasticsear
       ch - Offical Elasticsearch client library
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/UnQLite]UnQLite

Date & Time

   Libraries for working with dates and times
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DateTime]DateTime
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Time::Moment]Time::Moment
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Time::Piece]Time::Piece

Devices

   Libraries to talk to physical devices
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Device::Modem]Device::Modem - Talk to
       modem devices conneted via serial port
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Device::Onkyo]Device::Onkyo - Control
       Onkyo/Integra AV equipment via LAN or Serial

DevOps Tools

   Libraries that help when you what to deploy software across networks
   ond several hostsare working across computer networks
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Rex]Rex - Remote Execution

Email

   Libraries that implement email creation and sending
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Email::Sender]Email::Sender

Event Loops

   Libraries for various event loops. Asynchronous programming if you like
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/AE]AE - Simpler, faster, newer AnyEvent
       API
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/AnyEvent]AnyEvent - the DBI of event loop
       programming
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/EV]EV - Uses libev, very fast and
       popular. Default for AnyEvent if present
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Event]Event - Works well, but older
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/IO::Async]IO::Async - Asynchronous
       event-driven programming
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/POE]POE - Common interface for several
       event loops

Exception Handling

   Libraries that assist with and/or provide alternatives to eval{ die() }
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/autodie]autodie - Replace functions with
       ones that succeed or die with lexical scope
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Exception::Class]Exception::Class - A
       module that allows you to declare real exception classes in Perl
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Throwable]Throwable - a role for classes
       that can be thrown
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Try::Tiny]Try::Tiny - minimal try/catch
       with proper preservation of $@
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/TryCatch]TryCatch - first class try catch
       semantics for Perl, without source filters

File Manipulation

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/File::Util]File::Util - Easy, versatile,
       portable file handling.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Path::Tiny]Path::Tiny - Simple
       object-oriented file manipulation.

Form Frameworks

   Libraries that take the boredom & repetition out of (web and UI) forms
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Catalyst::Controller::HTML::FormFu]Cataly
       st::Controller::HTML::FormFu - Use HTML::FormFu in Catalyst.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/CGI::FormBuilder]CGI::FormBuilder -
       Easily generate and process stateful forms.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Form::Sensible]Form::Sensible - A
       sensible way to handle form based user interface.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Form::Toolkit]Form::Toolkit - A toolkit
       to build Data centric Forms.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/HTML::FormFu]HTML::FormFu - HTML Form
       Creation, Rendering and Validation Framework.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/HTML::FormFu::ExtJS]HTML::FormFu::ExtJS -
       ExtJS form generation from HTML::FormFu config files.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/HTML::FormHandler]HTML::FormHandler -
       HTML forms using Moose.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mojolicious::Plugin::FormFields]Mojolicio
       us::Plugin::FormFields - Lightweight, flexible form builder with
       validation and filtering.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/WWW::Form]WWW::Form - Simple and
       extendable module that allows developers to handle HTML form input
       validation and display flexibly and consistently.

Images

   Libraries for manipulating images
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Image::Magick]Image::Magick - An
       object-oriented interface to ImageMagick's image composing
       libraries.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Imager]Imager

List Manipulation

   Libraries for manipulation lists (arrays)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Array::Unique]Array::Unique - Tie-able
       array that allows only unique values
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/List::Compare]List::Compare - Compare
       elements of two or more lists
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/List::Gen]List::Gen - Provides functions
       for generating lists
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/List::MoreUtils]List::MoreUtils - Provide
       the stuff missing in List::Util
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/List::Util]List::Util - A selection of
       general-utility list subroutines

Logging

   Libraries for generating and working with log files
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Log::Dispatch]Log::Dispatch
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Log::Log4perl]Log::Log4perl
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Log::Minimal]Log::Minimal

Module Development

   Libraries that simplify and improve Perl module development
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Dist::Zilla]Dist::Zilla -
       [http://dzil.org/]http://dzil.org/
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Minilla]Minilla - CPAN module authoring
       tool

Network

   Libraries that help when you are dealing with computer networks
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DOCSIS::ConfigFile]DOCSIS::ConfigFile -
       Decodes and encodes DOCSIS config files
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/NetAddr::MAC]NetAddr::MAC - Handle MAC
       addresses

   Libraries that help when you are working across computer networks
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::SSH::Perl]Net::SSH::Perl - SSH
       client implemented in Perl.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::SSH2]Net::SSH2 - Wrapper for
       [https://libssh2.org/]libssh2.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::OpenSSH]Net::OpenSSH - Run commands
       remotely using the [http://www.openssh.com/]OpenSSH client.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::OpenSSH::Parallel]Net::OpenSSH::Para
       llel - Run remote commands in parallel using the OpenSSH client.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::SSH::Any]Net::SSH::Any - Run remote
       commands using any module or binary client available.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::SFTP::Foreign]Net::SFTP::Foreign -
       SFTP client for remote file access.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Object::Remote]Object::Remote - Run Perl
       code on remote machines.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::CLI::Interact]Net::CLI::Interact -
       Automates interactive programs.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::Appliance::Session]Net::Appliance::S
       ession - Automates interaction with appliances.

ORM

   Libraries that implement Object-Relational Mapping or datamapping
   techniques
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIx::Class]DBIx::Class
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Rose::DB]Rose::DB
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Teng]Teng

Package Management

   Libraries for package and dependency management
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/App::cpanminus]App::cpanminus
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Carton]Carton
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Pinto]Pinto - Powerful local CPAN repos

Processes and Threads

   Libraries for managing processes and threads
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Parallel::ForkManager]Parallel::ForkManag
       er - A simple parallel processing fork manager
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Parallel::Prefork]Parallel::Prefork - A
       simple prefork server framework
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Proclet]Proclet - Minimalistic
       supervisor, a Perl port of
       [https://github.com/ddollar/foreman]foreman

Profiling

   Libraries for examining run-time activity of your program
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::KYTProf]Devel::KYTProf - Very
       light profiler for I/Os such as HTTP request-responses and SQL
       queries.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::NYTProf]Devel::NYTProf - Code
       profiler.

Protocol

   Protocol clients and libraries
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Furl]Furl - Faster HTTP(S) Client
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/HTTP::Tiny]HTTP::Tiny - Minimal and fast
       client. Included in the standard packages.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/LWP::UserAgent]LWP::UserAgent - Popular
       HTTP(S) Client
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::DHCP]Net::DHCP - Send and recieve
       DHCP packets
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::DNS]Net::DNS - Resolve DNS host
       names

Queueing

   Message Queue, Job Queue System..
