       framework for Perl
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Squatting]Squatting - A Camping-inspired
       Web Microframework for Perl

Template Engines

   Libraries and tools for templating
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/HTML::Template]HTML::Template - Templates
       for web pages
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Template::Alloy]Template::Alloy - TT2/3,
       HT, HTE, Tmpl, and Velocity Engine
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Template::Toolkit]Template::Toolkit -
       Very Popular Template Processing System
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::MicroTemplate]Text::MicroTemplate -
       Fast, simple and safe template engine written in pure-Perl and core
       modules.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::MicroTemplate::Extended]Text::Micro
       Template::Extended - Extended Text::MicroTemplate.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::Template]Text::Template - Templates
       with embedded perl
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Text::Xslate]Text::Xslate - Faster
       template engine with XS. Supports multiple syntaxes.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Tiffany]Tiffany - Generic interface for
       template engines. It makes it easy to use multiple template
       engines.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Template::Magic]Template::Magic - Magic
       merger of runtime values with templates.

Testing

   Libraries for testing codebases and generating test data.

Testing Frameworks

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Base]Test::Base - A Data Driven
       Testing Framework
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Base::Less]Test::Base::Less -
       Limited version of Test::Base
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::BDD::Cucumber]Test::BDD::Cucumber -
       Implementation of the popular Cucumber framework in Perl
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Class]Test::Class - Class-based
       testing. Support "setup" and "teardown".
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Deep]Test::Deep - Test deep and
       complex data structures with great flexibility.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Deep::Matcher]Test::Deep::Matcher
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Harness]Test::Harness - Run Perl
       standard test scripts with statistics
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Kantan]Test::Kantan - simple,
       flexible, fun "Testing framework"
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::More]Test::More

Test Double

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Exception]Test::Exception
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Fatal]Test::Fatal - Simple module
       for verifying exceptions.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Mock::Guard]Test::Mock::Guard -
       Mocking package subroutines.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::MockTime]Test::MockTime
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::mysqld]Test::mysqld
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::TCP]Test::TCP - Launch temporary
       TCP Server
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Test::Time]Test::Time - Simple module for
       faking system time.

Coverage

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::Cover]Devel::Cover
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::Cover::Report::Coveralls]Devel::Co
       ver::Report::Coveralls Report to Coveralls

Tools

   Some useful tools
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/App::Ack]App::Ack - ack is a tool like
       grep, optimized for programmers.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/App::Nopaste]App::Nopaste - Post to
       various pastebins from the CLI
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Daiku]Daiku - Make for Perl.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Data::Printer]Data::Printer - Colored
       pretty-print of Perl data structures and objects.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Reply]Reply - Read-eval-print-loop(REPL)
       command-line tool.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Riji]Riji - Static site generator using
       markdown and git mainly for blogging.

   Libraries for developping command line applications
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Toolbox::Simple]Toolbox::Simple - Simplfy
       some common tasks in Perl.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Script::Toolbox]Script::Toolbox -
       Framework for the daily business scripts.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Devel::Kit]Devel::Kit- Handy toolbox of
       things to ease development/debugging.

   Libraries for handling configuration files
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Config::Tiny]Config::Tiny - Read/Write
       .ini style files with as little code as possible

Video

     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/FFmpeg]FFmpeg - Interface to FFmpeg, a
       video converter written in C
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Video::Info]Video::Info - Retrieve video
       properties such as: height width codec fps

Web Frameworks

   Libraries for developing Web applications
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Amon2]Amon2
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Catalyst]Catalyst - Overflowing with
       features. Very popular.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Dancer]Dancer
       ([http://perldancer.org/]Official site)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Dancer2]Dancer2
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Gantry]Gantry - Web application framework
       for mod_perl, cgi, etc.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Kossy]Kossy - A Web framework with simple
       interface.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mojolicious]Mojolicious - An all in one
       framework.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Poet]Poet - a modern Perl web framework
       for Mason developers

Middlewares

   Libraries for creating HTTP middlewares
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Gazelle]Gazelle - Preforked Plack Handler
       for performance freaks
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Plack]Plack - PSGI server implementation
       and utilities for Web applications.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Server::Starter]Server::Starter - Process
       manager with the "graceful restart" feature.
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Starlet]Starlet - High-performance PSGI
       Server
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Starman]Starman - High-performance
       preforking PSGI/Plack web server
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Twiggy]Twiggy - Event-driven PSGI
       application server

Web Frameworks-Like

   Somewhere between templates and full on frameworks
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Embperl]Embperl - Building dynamic
       Websites with Perl (sort of like Perl crossed with PHP)
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Mason]Mason - Powerful, high-performance
       templating for the web and beyond

Web Scraping

   Libraries for extracting some information from websites
     * [https://metacpan.org/pod/Web::Scraper]Web::Scraper

